ALZA Corp said it has notifiedthe State of California Regional Water Quality Control Board ofa plan to remedy groundwater and soil contamination it detectedat a site in Stanford Research Park.    A preliminary water sample showed water apparentlycontaminated some years ago with the industrial solventchloroform. The company said the contamination does not affectdrinking water or water used its operations on the site.    The plan is expected to cost a maximum of 750,000 dlrs, thecompany said. Reuter&#3;